Reasoning: The paper describes a software framework for integrating the results of the meta-theory of structural operational semantics (SOS) and its implementation in Maude. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the automatic derivation of sound and ground-complete axiomatizations for languages, which could also place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Language and Computation (cs.LG) sub-category, given its focus on language constructs and their semantic properties.
